  "texts": [
    "(a), (b): Logarithm of the electronic quasimomentum distribution n k (t) as a function of time for a small (J/t0 = 0.9) and a large (J/t0 = 3.0) Kondo coupling, respectively.",
    "After a fast initial dynamics, n k (t) exhibits two well-defined peaks at k = -π/2 + J/4, and k = π/2 -J/4 for the case of (a).",
    "These finite-momentum peaks are inconsistent with a thermal state in the steady-state regime.",
    "In (c), we illustrate the time evolution of n k,↑ (t) at momentum k = π/2 for both values of J.",
    "We set L = 216, k0 = π/2, and an initial ferromagnetic configuration for the localized spins, i.e., |Ψ0,F ⟩."
